  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F) and grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Shred the red cabbage with a sharp knife or food processor.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat; add sliced onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add minced garlic, cumin, coriander, and black pepper, cooking for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Stir in shredded cabbage, salt, lemon zest, and vinegar; cook for 3-4 minutes until the cabbage begins to soften.",
    "Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish; pour lemon juice and water evenly over the cabbage.",
    "Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes. Remove foil, stir, and bake another 10-15 minutes until the cabbage is tender and lightly caramelized.",
    "Let rest 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
